@node PLOT "Plot"

@{b}@{u}"UsePlugin" name:@{uu}@{ub}

    UsePlugin 'plot'

@{b}@{u}Command template:@{uu}@{ub}

    PLOT    X/N/A,Y/N/A

@{b}@{u}Function:@{uu}@{ub}

    Set a point in the current forground color.

@{b}@{u}Parameters:@{uu}@{ub}

    X,Y     Coordinates of point.

@endnode

@node BOOLE "Boole"

@{b}@{u}"UsePlugin" name:@{uu}@{ub}

    UsePlugin 'logic'   (Ha! That`s something new!)

@{b}@{u}Command template:@{uu}@{ub}

    BOOLE   AND/S,OR/S,NOT/S,XOR/S

@{b}@{u}Function:@{uu}@{ub}

    Combine the current buffer with the secondary buffer by a logical
    operation. @{i}Note:@{ui} Both buffers @{b}must@{ub} have the same size.

@{b}@{u}Parameters:@{uu}@{ub}
@endnode

@node MIX "Mix"

@{b}@{u}"UsePlugin" name:@{uu}@{ub}

    UsePlugin 'mix'

@{b}@{u}Command template:@{uu}@{ub}

    MIX

@{b}@{u}Function:@{uu}@{ub}

    Mixes the current buffer with the secondary via alpha channel.
    @{i}Note:@{ui} Both buffers @{b}must@{ub} have the same size.

@endnode

@node ERROR "Error"

Whenever an error is encountered, the variable sfilter.lasterror is set.
The error level will always be set to 10. The following errors can
be encountered:

    @{b}E01: Unknown command @{i}command@{ui}.@{ub}
    The command @{i}command@{ui} is not an sfilter command. Note that
    this error is also issued when a plugin is not loaded.

    @{b}E02: Can`t load frame @{i}file@{ui}@{ub}
    The file can`t be loaded. It`s either not there, or too large
    to fit into memory,

    @{b}E03: Can`t create buffer@{ub}
    There is either not enough memory to create the buffer, or the
    default keyword was given with no default frame in memory.

    @{b}E04: Plugin @{i}plugin@{ui} reported error@{ub}
    The plugin could not execute the operation. This can have many reasons,
    including a missing secondary buffer, or parameters that were out of
    range.

    @{b}E05: Plugin library @{i}plugin@{ui} not found@{ub}
    The plugin was not found in the plugin directory.

    @{b}E06: No frame to work on@{ub}
    No frame was loaded, so nothing can be done.

    @{b}E07: Can`t open font @{i}font@{ui}@{ub}
    The requested font could not be loaded.

    @{b}E08: No font@{ub}
    No font was loaded when trying to print.

    @{b}E09: Can`t open object map@{ub}
    The object map could not be loaded. Either the file was not found, or
    there was not enough memory available.

    @{b}E10: No default buffer@{ub}
    The default buffer was not loaded. Load it with @{"LoadFrame" link LOADFRAME}.

    @{b}E11: No buffer @{i}buffer@@{ui}@{ub}
    The buffer @{i}buffer@{ui} was not found.

    @{b}E12: Could not complete operation @{ub}
    The operation could not be completed (Ok, I know this is stupid, but
    who cares ?).

    @{b}E13: Buffers do not match@{ub}
    The buffers do not match in size.

    @{b}E14: No alpha channel@{ub}
    You tried an operation requiring an alpha channel without creating one.

    @{b}E15: no pen given@{ub}
    This error is obsolete in the latest version.

    @{b}E16: No such object@{ub}
    The named object could not be found in the loaded object map.

    @{b}E17: Can`t save file@{ub}
    The buffer could not be save. This can have several reasons, including
    memory shortage, not enough space on the device, or a locked file.



@endnode

